OtherAssetsOrgGrp.Desc: BENEFICIAL INTEREST IN ASSETS HELD BY MADISON COMMUNITY FOUNDATION

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: IN CONFORMITY WITH ASC 958-360-25, THE ART COLLECTIONS, WHICH WERE ACQUIRED THROUGH PURCHASES AND CONTRIBUTIONS SINCE THE ORGANIZATION'S INCEPTION, ARE NOT RECOGNIZED AS ASSETS ON THE STATEMENTS OF FINANCIAL POSITION. PURCHASES OF THE ART COLLECTION ITEMS ARE RECORDED AS DECREASES IN UNRESTRICTED NET ASSETS IN THE YEAR IN WHICH THE ITEMS ARE ACQUIRED, OR AS TEMPORARILY OR PERMANENTLY RESTRICTED NET ASSETS IF THE ASSETS USED TO PURCHASE THE ITEMS ARE RESTRICTED BY DONORS. CONTRIBUTED ART COLLECTION ITEMS ARE NOT REFLECTED ON THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. PROCEEDS FROM DEACCESSIONS OR INSURANCE RECOVERIES ARE REFLECTED AS INCREASES IN THE APPROPRIATE NET ASSET CLASSES.
THE COLLECTION CONSISTS OF OVER 5,000 20TH CENTURY AND CONTEMPORARY ARTWORKS WITH A MAJORITY OF THEM PRINTS. THE MISSION OF THE MUSEUM IS TO EXHIBIT, EDUCATE AND COLLECT CONTEMPORARY AMERICAN ART.
THE ENDOWMENT FUNDS ARE HELD BY A RELATED PARTY AND THE MADISON COMMUNITY FOUNDATION AND ARE INTENDED TO PROVIDE EARNINGS TO BE USED IN CARRYING OUT THE OPERATIONAL MISSION OF THE MUSEUM.

IN CONFORMITY WITH ASC 958-360-25, THE ART COLLECTIONS REPORTED ON SCHEDULE M, PART I, LINE 1, ARE NOT RECOGNIZED AS ASSETS ON THE STATEMENTS OF FINANCIAL POSITION. CONTRIBUTED ART COLLECTION ITEMS ARE NOT REFLECTED ON THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PROCESS TO DETERMINE COMPENSATION IS THAT THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR PROVIDES A SELF-EVALUATION TO THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD AND THEY IN TURN PRESENT A WRITTEN EVALUATION OF THE DIRECTOR IN DETERMINING ANY ANNUAL CHANGE IN COMPENSATION.
